President Obama has announced a Presidential Delegation that will attend the inauguration of Pedro Pablo Kuczynski, President-elect of Peru, on July 28, 2016. The delegation will be led by Michael Froman, the U.S. Trade Representative, and will include members such as Brian A. Nichols, the U.S. Ambassador to Peru, William R. Brownfield, Assistant Secretary of State for International Narcotics and Law Enforcement Affairs, Lieutenant General Joseph P. DiSalvo, U.S. Army Military Deputy Commander, and Mari Carmen Aponte, Acting Assistant Secretary of State for Western Hemisphere Affairs.